WEBVTT

00:05.939 --> 00:08.375
[ Deep voice ] Hand it over --
everything of value.

00:09.209 --> 00:10.777
[ Bubbling ]

00:10.811 --> 00:11.978
[ Whimpers ]

00:12.012 --> 00:13.714
I said everything!

00:13.747 --> 00:15.549
Is this
really necessary, Mom?

00:15.582 --> 00:17.017
I'm not taking
any chances.

00:17.050 --> 00:19.420
But he's my father!
He's not gonna steal from us.

00:19.453 --> 00:21.154
Richard,
he's a con artist.

00:21.187 --> 00:23.757
That 24-karat necklace he sold
you was made of actual carrots.

00:23.790 --> 00:26.192
Yeah, but at least
I remembered your birthday.

00:26.226 --> 00:29.095
Come on. He invited us over.
He's making an effort.

00:29.129 --> 00:30.431
He probably wants
something from us.

00:30.464 --> 00:31.832
Or sell something
to us.

00:31.865 --> 00:33.299
Or sell one of us.

00:33.333 --> 00:35.101
GPS: You have arrived
at your destination.

00:35.135 --> 00:36.302
[ Crash ]

00:36.336 --> 00:38.204
It is an awful neighborhood.

00:38.238 --> 00:40.707
Does Grandpa Frankie
really live in there?

00:40.741 --> 00:42.543
It could be worse.
He could live in that.

00:42.576 --> 00:43.744
[ Knocks ]

00:43.777 --> 00:45.646
Hello, Wattersons!

00:45.679 --> 00:46.847
[ Sighs ]

00:46.880 --> 00:48.014
Come on in!

00:48.048 --> 00:50.283
Oh. Excuse
the houseguests.

00:50.316 --> 00:53.019
[ Shuddering ]

00:53.053 --> 00:55.155
Frankie:
So, let me give you a tour.

00:55.188 --> 00:56.657
Here's the living area...

00:56.690 --> 00:59.059
and that's
the end of the tour.

00:59.092 --> 01:00.527
It's...uh...

01:00.561 --> 01:04.064
Well, it might not be much,
but it's home for me --

01:04.097 --> 01:06.633
and about 25 different species
of parasite.

01:06.667 --> 01:08.101
[ Quietly ]
26, including you.

01:08.134 --> 01:09.235
[ Inhales sharply ]

01:09.269 --> 01:10.737
It's good to see you,
Pop.

01:10.771 --> 01:12.839
Nice to have the family
all together.

01:12.873 --> 01:16.242
I was gonna get in touch sooner,
but my phone broke.

01:16.276 --> 01:17.644
Anyway, you guys hungry?

01:17.678 --> 01:18.845
All: Sure!

01:18.879 --> 01:20.514
Me too.

01:20.547 --> 01:23.116
I thought there'd be some food
coming after that question.

01:23.149 --> 01:24.918
No, just sad music.

01:24.951 --> 01:26.419
[ Melancholy music plays ]

01:26.453 --> 01:28.989
O...kay.
How about a glass of water?

01:29.022 --> 01:30.624
Sure.
Where are you going?

01:30.657 --> 01:32.392
I get my water
from the toilets.

01:32.425 --> 01:34.427
I'll boil it
when I get back.

01:34.461 --> 01:36.597
Is anyone thinking
what I'm thinking?
Yeah.

01:36.630 --> 01:37.864
This is great!
Let's leave now.

01:37.898 --> 01:39.500
Wait. What?! Wait. What?!

01:39.533 --> 01:42.503
Richard, listen, I'm gonna try
and say this as nicely as I can.

01:42.536 --> 01:45.071
This place is worse
than a Porta-Potty
at a punk music festival

01:45.105 --> 01:47.273
that's been left
stewing in the sun for a week.

01:47.307 --> 01:49.075
Wow! What was
the harsh version like?

01:49.109 --> 01:51.377
I would have expanded
on what the punks did inside.

01:51.411 --> 01:52.579
Don't you get it?

01:52.613 --> 01:53.947
He lives
in a confined space,

01:53.980 --> 01:56.750
he's not used to
modern technology, and look.

01:56.783 --> 01:59.119
Two rats roasting a cockroach
over an open fire?

01:59.152 --> 02:01.622
[ Both screech ]
No -- those.

02:01.655 --> 02:03.590
The bars on the windows.
Hmm.

02:03.624 --> 02:06.359
Where did Grandpa say he was all
those years when he was away?

02:06.392 --> 02:08.161
I don't know --
he just said he was somewhere

02:08.194 --> 02:09.663
no one could contact him
or visit.

02:09.696 --> 02:11.965
[ Gasps ] Don't you see?
He was in prison!

02:11.998 --> 02:14.400
He can't do anything
for himself anymore.

02:14.434 --> 02:16.670
He needs routine and
people telling him what to do.

02:16.703 --> 02:18.805
We should create
a familiar environment for him.

02:18.839 --> 02:20.507
Where?
Home.

02:20.541 --> 02:22.475
We need to bring
Grandpa Frankie home --

02:22.509 --> 02:23.744
our home.

02:23.777 --> 02:24.578
Yes!

02:24.611 --> 02:25.679
Ohh!

02:28.448 --> 02:29.816
Oh, hey, Anais!

02:29.850 --> 02:31.818
It sure is kind of you guys
to invite me --

02:31.852 --> 02:33.820
It's "Miss Watterson"
to you, perp!

02:33.854 --> 02:36.022
Walk and talk with me.
I haven't got all day.

02:36.056 --> 02:37.591
Huh. Rude.

02:37.624 --> 02:39.159
Okay, you're going inside.

02:39.192 --> 02:40.994
Keep your nose clean, your head
down, and, with good behavior,

02:41.027 --> 02:43.630
you'll be out of here in time
for my graduation ceremony.

02:43.664 --> 02:44.698
Right.

02:44.731 --> 02:46.700
Operation Make Grandpa Frankie
Feel At Home

02:46.733 --> 02:48.669
By Turning Our House
Into A Prison is a go.

02:48.702 --> 02:50.403
I just wish
it had a catchier title.

02:50.436 --> 02:52.038
[ Doorbell rings ]

02:53.106 --> 02:55.842
Oh, hey, Nicole.
I hope I'm not late for dinner.

02:55.876 --> 02:56.977
Hand it over!

02:57.010 --> 02:58.078
Uh...thanks?

02:58.111 --> 02:59.245
And the rest.

02:59.279 --> 03:00.747
Oh.

03:04.718 --> 03:06.219
[ Zipper opens ]

03:06.252 --> 03:07.588
Too much.
Sorry.

03:07.621 --> 03:09.422
Careful when you launder
that shirt, doll.

03:09.455 --> 03:10.724
It's real silk.

03:10.757 --> 03:13.159
So, uh,
where is everyone?

03:13.193 --> 03:14.561
And what's with the face?

03:14.595 --> 03:17.631
I got a warmer reception
at the igloo convention!

03:19.065 --> 03:21.668
Which is actually a thing,
by the way.

03:23.269 --> 03:25.572
How about
you fix us a drink?

03:26.506 --> 03:27.908
[ Coughing ]
Put that on!

03:27.941 --> 03:28.975
A gift?

03:29.009 --> 03:30.143
Too kind.

03:30.176 --> 03:31.678
I think
I just shed a tear.

03:31.712 --> 03:33.980
Although, my face is wet,
so it's hard to tell.

03:34.014 --> 03:35.181
You sleep here.

03:35.215 --> 03:36.482
Thanks, Nicole.

03:36.516 --> 03:38.484
And can I just say that --
[ Door slams ]

03:38.518 --> 03:40.353
I guess I can't.

03:41.387 --> 03:42.956
[ Gruffly ] Hmph.
Oh, hey, kid.

03:42.989 --> 03:44.357
Looks like we're sharing.

03:44.390 --> 03:45.458
Nice tattoos.

03:45.491 --> 03:46.860
What's that one?

03:46.893 --> 03:49.462
That's a portrait of my girl.
She's waitin' for me.

03:49.495 --> 03:51.397
Quite the looker.
And that one?

03:51.431 --> 03:53.299
A unicorn
battling another unicorn.

03:53.333 --> 03:54.935
Means I'll always
defend my homies.

03:54.968 --> 03:55.802
And that?

03:55.836 --> 03:57.503
A lion
with a baseball bat,

03:57.537 --> 03:59.272
so people know
not to mess with me.

03:59.305 --> 04:02.142
Kind of looks like a butt
with a wig playing the oboe.

04:02.175 --> 04:03.777
[ Normal voice ] Does it?
Yeah.

04:03.810 --> 04:06.179
Well, it's hard to draw
on your own back, okay?!

04:06.212 --> 04:07.513
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

04:07.547 --> 04:09.716
Why is everyone so tense
around here?

04:09.750 --> 04:10.984
And what's up with him?

04:11.017 --> 04:14.187
[ Growling wheezily ]

04:14.220 --> 04:15.822
[ Gruffly ] Yeah,
I wouldn't mess with that one.

04:15.856 --> 04:18.191
He belongs in a more padded
cell, if you catch my drift.

04:18.224 --> 04:19.826
So do you.

04:19.860 --> 04:21.995
[ Normal voice ] Aw! You think
I'm criminally insane, too!

04:22.028 --> 04:23.463
Thanks.

04:23.496 --> 04:25.298
I...think
I'm going to bed.

04:25.331 --> 04:26.499
Hey!
[ Groans ]

04:26.532 --> 04:28.234
I get the top bunk,
fish!

04:28.268 --> 04:29.870
Ohhh!
What is this?

04:29.903 --> 04:31.071
Shower gel in a sock.

04:31.104 --> 04:32.272
I couldn't find any soap.

04:32.305 --> 04:34.474
Oh, whatever.
Good night.

04:35.909 --> 04:37.377
[ Door opens ]

04:37.410 --> 04:39.045
[ Footsteps ]

04:39.079 --> 04:40.781
[ Floorboards creak ]

04:40.814 --> 04:42.082
Hey, Pop.

04:42.115 --> 04:43.383
How you holding up?

04:43.416 --> 04:45.719
They say the first night's
the hardest.

04:45.752 --> 04:48.454
[ Whispering ]
But don't worry. I got ya.

04:48.488 --> 04:49.856
Mom: Lights out!!

04:49.890 --> 04:51.391
[ Door slams ]

04:51.424 --> 04:54.260
[ Birds chirping ]

04:54.294 --> 04:55.696
Mom:
Rise and shine, maggots!

04:55.729 --> 04:57.263
Ow!
Hurry up, Pop.

04:57.297 --> 05:00.066
You don't want to find out
what happens if you're late.

05:00.100 --> 05:02.202
And it's your turn
to empty the bucket.

05:02.235 --> 05:03.069
Ugh!

05:03.103 --> 05:05.638
Finally -- some privacy.

05:05.672 --> 05:08.274
[ Muffled ] Hey, Pop.
We all shower together here.

05:08.308 --> 05:09.542
Can you do my back?

05:09.575 --> 05:11.377
Uh...sure.

05:11.411 --> 05:12.879
Thanks.

05:15.215 --> 05:17.117
So, what's for breakfast,
doll?

05:17.150 --> 05:19.085
Waffles?
French toast?

05:19.119 --> 05:20.687
Froot Loops?

05:20.721 --> 05:23.123
It doesn't look good,
but I'm sure it tastes...

05:23.156 --> 05:24.825
[ Slurps ] Nope.

05:24.858 --> 05:27.660
So, not that I really mind, but
aren't you gonna eat with us?

05:27.694 --> 05:29.595
I don't eat with you.
I'm not your friend.

05:29.629 --> 05:31.798
I don't even want to see you
unless I have to.

05:31.832 --> 05:32.799
[ Grunts ]

05:32.833 --> 05:34.667
Hmm. I think
she's warming to me.

05:34.701 --> 05:35.802
Eeeh.

05:35.836 --> 05:37.403
Uh, do you mind
if I sit in that chair?

05:37.437 --> 05:38.604
[ Gruffly ] Yes!

05:38.638 --> 05:40.073
[ Sighs ] Right.

05:43.376 --> 05:44.711
[ Sighs ]

05:44.745 --> 05:47.280
I think
I've lost my appetite.

05:47.313 --> 05:48.548
Thanks, Pop.

05:48.581 --> 05:50.216
[ Pounding ]

05:51.351 --> 05:55.155
Uh, isn't that a bit risky
for a kid with only one finger?

05:55.188 --> 05:57.390
I wouldn't make eye contact
with him.
Why?

05:57.423 --> 06:00.460
[ Screams ]

06:00.493 --> 06:01.862
Ohh!

06:01.895 --> 06:03.463
Mom: No sleeping
in the canteen!

06:03.496 --> 06:04.664
Yard -- now!

06:04.697 --> 06:06.299
I can't believe
I'm saying this,

06:06.332 --> 06:09.269
but I think you're becoming
my favorite in this family.

06:09.302 --> 06:10.837
I said now!

06:10.871 --> 06:13.339
Mm...feels like
we're being a bit mean to him.

06:13.373 --> 06:14.540
What makes you
say that?

06:14.574 --> 06:16.142
Eh...I know my dad.

06:16.176 --> 06:18.879
I can sense a subtle sadness
in his eyes.

06:18.912 --> 06:21.281
[ Sobbing ]

06:21.314 --> 06:22.849
Leave this to me.

06:24.317 --> 06:27.020
[ Gruffly ]
Psst. I stole some cookies
from the commissary.

06:27.053 --> 06:29.255
Want some?
[ Sniffles ] For real?

06:29.289 --> 06:30.824
Yeah, man.
Here you go.

06:30.857 --> 06:32.592
[ Gasps ]

06:32.625 --> 06:33.626
Thanks.

06:33.659 --> 06:34.895
See you later.

06:34.928 --> 06:37.063
I'm not finished yet.
What do you mean?

06:37.097 --> 06:38.899
Contraband!

06:38.932 --> 06:39.800
[ Panting ]

06:39.833 --> 06:41.001
You're going
in the hole!

06:41.034 --> 06:42.602
Why are you doing this
to me?!

06:42.635 --> 06:43.669
[ Door slams ]

06:43.703 --> 06:45.071
[ Pounding on door ]
Let me out!

06:45.105 --> 06:48.008
Will someone let me out?!

06:50.343 --> 06:51.344
[ Sighs ]

06:51.377 --> 06:53.780
Okay,
Mr., uh, Watterson.

06:53.814 --> 06:55.681
I hear you have
some complaints about

06:55.715 --> 06:57.217
how we run things
around here.

06:57.250 --> 06:58.551
You bet I do!

06:58.584 --> 07:00.120
They hosed me down,
they fed me slop,

07:00.153 --> 07:01.621
they made me shower
with them,

07:01.654 --> 07:03.056
and look at me
like I'm the weirdo.

07:03.089 --> 07:05.258
They insulted me,
they stole my clothes,

07:05.291 --> 07:06.659
they locked me in here,

07:06.692 --> 07:09.595
and this time, they didn't even
give me a bucket!

07:09.629 --> 07:11.631
Hold on.
I need more fingers.

07:11.664 --> 07:14.901
Even that's not enough to count
all the things they did to me.

07:14.935 --> 07:16.436
Wait.
Are you doodling?

07:16.469 --> 07:19.605
Yes. It's a picture of you
playing a tiny violin!

07:19.639 --> 07:21.507
Like it?

07:21.541 --> 07:22.976
I'm running
a correctional facility,

07:23.009 --> 07:25.311
not some kindergarten
for whining man-babies!

07:25.345 --> 07:26.646
Wait a minute.

07:26.679 --> 07:29.349
I'm asking a 4-year-old
to get me out of a shed,

07:29.382 --> 07:31.017
when I could just leave.

07:32.718 --> 07:34.354
Mom: Where do you think
you're going?!

07:34.387 --> 07:36.990
Richard, your family
is deranged!

07:37.023 --> 07:38.558
This place is
like a prison!

07:38.591 --> 07:39.759
I'm out of here!

07:39.792 --> 07:41.895
Wait!
Family huddle.

07:41.928 --> 07:44.865
Guys, I think there's a slim
possibility that maybe we are

07:44.898 --> 07:48.101
♪ absolutely nailing it!

07:48.134 --> 07:49.469
Good work, everyone!

07:49.502 --> 07:51.504
You're going nowhere,
Watterson!

07:51.537 --> 07:52.705
Says who?

07:52.738 --> 07:54.674
[ Screaming ]

07:54.707 --> 07:55.675
Too much?

07:55.708 --> 07:56.709
All: Nah.

07:56.742 --> 07:58.879
[ Snoring ]

07:58.912 --> 08:01.214
[ Groans ] My head!

08:01.247 --> 08:04.150
Well, at least
it can't get any worse.

08:04.184 --> 08:05.385
[ Moans ]

08:05.418 --> 08:06.920
[ Groans ]

08:06.953 --> 08:09.222
[ Watch beeps ]
Okay,
it's 4:00 in the morning.

08:09.255 --> 08:11.958
Time for Grandpa Frankie's
gentle wake-up call.

08:11.992 --> 08:13.927
Rise and shine,
you maggots!

08:13.960 --> 08:16.496
[ Gasps ]
He escaped!

08:16.529 --> 08:17.697
Hmm.

08:17.730 --> 08:20.466
[ Gasps ]
Of course! The poster!

08:20.500 --> 08:21.834
The window, Dad.

08:21.868 --> 08:23.669
Of course!
The window!

08:23.703 --> 08:24.670
[ Coughs ]

08:24.704 --> 08:25.738
Never mind.

08:25.771 --> 08:27.473
Sound the alarm!

08:27.507 --> 08:29.142
[ Watch beeping ]

08:29.175 --> 08:31.344
We're gonna need
something bigger.

08:31.377 --> 08:34.447
[ Alarm blaring ]

08:34.480 --> 08:35.748
So, where are we
gonna lay low?

08:35.781 --> 08:37.884
Bolivia? Mexico?
Chipotle?

08:37.918 --> 08:39.419
I got to
get these handcuffs off.

08:39.452 --> 08:41.787
So we go to a crooked
blacksmith? Bribe a lumberjack?

08:41.821 --> 08:43.957
No! We just go
to the police!

08:43.990 --> 08:45.858
So, Officer,
allow me to explain why

08:45.892 --> 08:48.561
I'm running through the streets
in a striped jumpsuit

08:48.594 --> 08:50.463
handcuffed
to a tattooed delinquent.

08:50.496 --> 08:51.464
Ehh!

08:51.497 --> 08:52.698
[ Panting ]

08:52.732 --> 08:53.766
[ Engine revving,
siren wailing ]

08:53.799 --> 08:55.501
[ Panting ]

08:55.535 --> 08:57.837
[ Tires screech ]

09:01.707 --> 09:04.877
I'm in pursuit of a fugitive
handcuffed to a tattooed child!

09:04.911 --> 09:06.446
Dispatcher:
You mean a 12-57?

09:06.479 --> 09:08.214
Uh...if you say so.

09:08.248 --> 09:09.715
[ Panting ]

09:13.353 --> 09:14.988
[ Tires screech ]

09:15.021 --> 09:16.556
Stop!

09:16.589 --> 09:18.258
Release the hound.

09:18.291 --> 09:20.660
[ Barking ]

09:20.693 --> 09:22.495
[ Barking continues ]

09:22.528 --> 09:25.098
Come on!
We'll lose them in here.

09:26.099 --> 09:27.633
These tunnels
go on for --

09:27.667 --> 09:28.868
Mom: Freeze!

09:28.901 --> 09:30.703
End of the line,
dirtball!

09:30.736 --> 09:33.273
Get back!
You people are insane!

09:33.306 --> 09:35.708
If you come any closer,
we'll jump!

09:35.741 --> 09:37.177
What?!
We haven't discussed this!

09:37.210 --> 09:39.112
Frankie, no!
We're not insane.

09:39.145 --> 09:40.513
We were doing it
for you --

09:40.546 --> 09:42.682
to make you feel like
you were in prison again.

09:42.715 --> 09:44.985
Prison?!
I never went to prison.

09:45.018 --> 09:48.221
Then, where were you
when Dad was growing up?

09:48.254 --> 09:50.756
I was running away
from prison.

09:50.790 --> 09:52.525
I got sentenced
to three days in jail

09:52.558 --> 09:55.661
for selling parcels of the moon
to senior citizens.

09:55.695 --> 09:57.230
Then, if you weren't
in prison,

09:57.263 --> 09:59.032
how come you can't cope
with living on the outside?

09:59.065 --> 10:02.035
I was trying to get free rent
and food out of you, okay?

10:02.068 --> 10:05.071
[ Scoffs ] He was trying
to scam us! I told you!

10:05.105 --> 10:07.673
Aw, Dad.
You should have just asked.

10:07.707 --> 10:09.342
You can stay with us
whenever you want.

10:09.375 --> 10:12.112
In fact, why don't you
come and live with us?

10:12.145 --> 10:13.713
[ Echoing ]
...live with us?

10:13.746 --> 10:14.914
...live with us?

10:14.947 --> 10:16.316
...live with us?

10:16.349 --> 10:17.517
...live with us?

10:17.550 --> 10:18.718
...live with us?

10:18.751 --> 10:20.020
...live with us?

10:20.053 --> 10:21.521
...live with us?

10:21.554 --> 10:22.722
...live with us?

10:22.755 --> 10:23.923
...live with us?

10:23.956 --> 10:25.325
...live with us?

10:25.358 --> 10:26.326
...live with us?

10:26.359 --> 10:27.527
...live with us?

10:27.560 --> 10:28.561
Nah.

10:28.594 --> 10:31.064
[ Screaming ]
[ All gasp ]

10:31.097 --> 10:32.965
Uh...
All: Hmm?

10:32.999 --> 10:35.501
Selling the moon
to senior citizens, eh?

10:35.535 --> 10:37.437
You're going to prison!

10:37.470 --> 10:38.671
No rent, free food.

10:38.704 --> 10:39.939
Why not?

10:41.974 --> 10:44.210
♪♪
